# agent-browser Defaults

## Launch

Always headed, always sandbox-disabled, always test-user auth:

```bash
agent-browser --headed open "http://localhost:3000/route?e2e_auto_login=true"
```

Every `agent-browser` Bash call requires `dangerouslyDisableSandbox: true` — the socket dir `~/.agent-browser` is outside the sandbox.

## URL Params

| Param | Effect |
|-------|--------|
| `e2e_auto_login=true` | Auto-login as test user (required) |
| `e2e_sidebar=open` | Auto-open sidebar after auth |
| `e2e_goto=first-memory` | Navigate to first memory after auth |

## `window.__e2e` Helpers

Available after auth completes. Use via `agent-browser eval "window.__e2e.methodName()"`.

Sidebar: `openSidebar()`, `closeSidebar()`, `isSidebarOpen()`
DOM: `has(testid)`, `lacks(testid)`, `getText(testid)`, `clickButton(label)`, `setInput(placeholder, value)`
Scroll: `scrollTo(selector)`, `getBox(selector)` → `"x,y,w,h"`
State: `isAuthComplete()`, `isAIResponseComplete()`, `getCompletedAIResponseCount()`
Compound: `clickFirstMemory()`, `findMemory(title)`, `installFetchInterceptor(urlPattern)`, `getFetchLogs()`, `clearFetchLogs()`
Mocks: `mockClipboard()` (fix headless clipboard), `mockFetchDelay(urlPattern, delayMs, response?)` (delay/mock API responses)

## Broken Commands

| Command | Why | Use instead |
|---------|-----|-------------|
| `scrollintoview @ref` | Crashes — parses ref as CSS selector | `eval "window.__e2e.scrollTo('selector')"` |
| `get box @ref` | Same crash | `eval "window.__e2e.getBox('selector')"` |
| `find role button click` | Doesn't register on many buttons | `eval "window.__e2e.clickButton('Label')"` |
| `--auto-connect` | Needs Chrome launched with debug port | `--headed open` |

## After Every Navigation

Refs go stale. Always re-snapshot:

```bash
agent-browser snapshot -i
```
